  "response_text": "Creating a healthy eating plan involves incorporating a variety of foods that provide the necessary nutrients while also considering personal preferences, dietary restrictions, and lifestyle. Below is a sample seven-day healthy eating plan that emphasizes whole foods, balanced meals, and portion control.\n\n### Healthy Eating Plan: 7-Day Sample Menu\n\n#### Day 1\n**Breakfast:**  \n- Greek yogurt with mixed berries and a tablespoon of honey  \n- A sprinkle of chia seeds  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- A small handful of almonds  \n\n**Lunch:**  \n- Quinoa salad with cherry tomatoes, cucumber, bell peppers, parsley, and a lemon-olive oil dressing  \n- Grilled chicken breast (or chickpeas for a vegetarian option)  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- Sliced apple with almond butter  \n\n**Dinner:**  \n- Baked salmon with a side of steamed broccoli and sweet potatoes  \n\n---\n\n#### Day 2\n**Breakfast:**  \n- Oatmeal topped with banana slices and a sprinkle of cinnamon  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- Carrot sticks with hummus  \n\n**Lunch:**  \n- Spinach and mixed greens salad with avocado, walnuts, feta cheese, and balsamic vinaigrette  \n- Whole grain bread on the side  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- Greek yogurt with a few walnuts  \n\n**Dinner:**  \n- Stir-fried tofu with mixed vegetables (bell peppers, broccoli, carrots) served over brown rice  \n\n---\n\n#### Day 3\n**Breakfast:**  \n- Smoothie with spinach, banana, protein powder, and almond milk  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- A small handful of mixed nuts  \n\n**Lunch:**  \n- Whole grain wrap with turkey, lettuce, tomato, and mustard  \n- Side of sliced cucumbers  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- Celery sticks with peanut butter  \n\n**Dinner:**  \n- Grilled shrimp with quinoa and asparagus  \n\n---\n\n#### Day 4\n**Breakfast:**  \n- Scrambled eggs with spinach and tomatoes  \n- Whole grain toast  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- A pear  \n\n**Lunch:**  \n- Lentil soup with a side of whole grain bread  \n- Mixed greens salad  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- Greek yogurt with a drizzle of honey  \n\n**Dinner:**  \n- Baked chicken thighs with roasted Brussels sprouts and carrots  \n\n---\n\n#### Day 5\n**Breakfast:**  \n- Chia pudding made with almond milk and topped with kiwi and coconut flakes  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- Sliced bell peppers with guacamole  \n\n**Lunch:**  \n- Brown rice bowl with black beans, corn, avocado, and salsa  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- A handful of trail mix (nuts and dried fruit)  \n\n**Dinner:**  \n- Grilled turkey burgers with a side of sweet potato fries  \n\n---\n\n#### Day 6\n**Breakfast:**  \n- Whole grain pancakes topped with fresh berries and a little maple syrup  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- Hard-boiled egg  \n\n**Lunch:**  \n- Tuna salad with mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, and olive oil dressing  \n- Whole grain crackers  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- Orange slices  \n\n**Dinner:**  \n- Vegetable stir-fry with tofu over whole grain noodles  \n\n---\n\n#### Day 7\n**Breakfast:**  \n- Smoothie bowl with blended banana, spinach, and almond milk topped with granola and seeds  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- A small handful of pistachios  \n\n**Lunch:**  \n- Chickpea salad with diced cucumbers, red onion, tomatoes, and a lemon-tahini dressing  \n\n**Snack:**  \n- Baby carrots with tzatziki sauce  \n\n**Dinner:**  \n- Baked cod with a side of wild rice and steamed green beans  \n\n---\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Hydration:** Aim to drink plenty of water throughout the day. Herbal teas and infused water can be great alternatives.\n- **Portion Control:** Be mindful of portion sizes, especially with high-calorie foods like nuts and dressings.\n- **Meal Prep:** Preparing meals in advance can help maintain healthy eating habits throughout the week.\n- **Listen to Your Body:** Pay attention to hunger and fullness cues to avoid overeating.\n- **Adaptability:** Feel free to swap similar meals or ingredients based on availability and personal preference.\n\n### Nutritional Considerations:\n- Make sure to include a variety of colors in fruits and vegetables to cover a spectrum of nutrients.\n- Incorporate sources of healthy fats (avocado, nuts, seeds) and lean proteins (fish, poultry, legumes) for balanced meals.\n- Limit added sugars and highly processed foods.\n\nThis plan can be adjusted based on individual needs, preferences, and any dietary restrictions. Always consult with a healthcare provider or a registered dietitian for personalized dietary advice.",
